The ChangeSummaryResult carries a per-event change summary describing the mutations the orchestrator applied (or would apply, in --dry-run preview). Its text body is the operation label followed by NodeChange entries (Kind: changed/added/removed; OldHash/NewHash truncated to 8 chars) and EdgeChange entries (Kind: added/removed; From, To). Hashes are truncated to 8 chars in all presenters so the summary stays scannable; full 40-char hashes remain available in state.xml and `drift list` for forensics. When Preview is true, the Plain and Color presenters prepend a "Preview — no changes written" banner; the JSON presenter sets a top-level `preview: true` field. Non-preview results carry the caller-supplied Message as a lead-in (e.g. "Closure a3f7b2c1 resolved."). JSON encodes the full ChangeSummary structurally. See <ref spec="cli.reset_format">reset format</ref>, <ref spec="cli.link_format">link format</ref>, <ref spec="cli.unlink_format">unlink format</ref>.